HEADWORD: Sway-backed
<hw>Sway"-backed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the back
hollow or sagged, whether naturally or as the result of injury or
weakness; -- said of horses and other animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

